interface ApiErrorProps {
  title?: string;
  subTitle?: string;
  onPress: () => void;
  hasBackToHome?: boolean;
  isLoading?: boolean;
  testID?: string;
  targetScreen?: keyof PropsRootStack;
}

interface ApiErrorViewProps extends ApiErrorProps {
  handleNavigateToHome: () => void;
}
```

### Default Values:
- `title = 'Ocorreu um erro inesperado'`
- `subTitle = 'Por favor, espere alguns minutos ou tente novamente.'`
- `hasBackToHome = true`
- `isLoading = false`
- `testID = 'ApiErrorView'`
- `targetScreen = 'Home'`

### What It Renders:
- Centered error layout with either:
  - Error image (188x188) when `hasBackToHome = true`
  - Red alert icon box when `hasBackToHome = false`
- Large title text (subtitleXXXXL)
- Optional subtitle text (paragraphXXL)
- "Tentar novamente" button (primary, with loading state)
- "Voltar para a home" button (ghost, only if `hasBackToHome = true`)

